'''Herman O. Ruhnau''' (, &ndash; , ) was a notable southern Californian post-modern architect.
Herman Ruhnau was born in Santa Barbara on the 1st of September 1912. He grew up in  and eventually studied architecture at the . He later served as an Architect in the Navy during . After the war he returned to Riverside where in the 1950's he founded the architectural firm now known as the Ruhnau Ruhnau Clarke.